    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 12 August 1534)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Since
                            <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>count
                            Maximilian’s<?oxy_custom_end?> men have arrived to buy a gyrfalcon,
                            Ghilino is taking the opportunity to write to Oláh. The Empress suffered
                            a stillbirth, which has saddened everyone. The Pope is suffering from
                            dysentery, and the physicians have given up on him, even if he is
                            somewhat better now. Hayreddin Barbarossa Pasha is said to be heading
                            for Malta. They have learned from a letter from Sicily that King Francis
                            I has sent Antonio Rincon to the Turks, and that the Sultan’s envoy
                            suffered a shipwreck on his way home and has been captured, but he has
                            been ransomed. Lodovico Gritti has arrived to Belgrade to mediate
                            between King Ferdinand I and Szapolyai, he wishes he was successful. He
                            would like to hear about the English affairs.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nicolao Olao salutem.</p>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Scripsi superioribus diebus ad te de omnibus rebus, quae hic
                    circumferebantur et litteris tuis, quas ad me <persName>Candiano</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.1">Ambrogio Candiano.</note> dedisti,
                        respondi.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Probably Ep. 490. and Ep.
                            491.<ref>olahus.tei.15340531_1</ref></note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15340531_2</ref>
                    Nunc venientibus istuc Maximiliani comitis familiaribus emptum hirifalcos<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.3">The gyrfalcon according to Hoven, i.e. the
                        largest of the falcon species (falco rusticolus). See <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Hoven</hi> 2006, 246.</note> non falcones, officii mei esse censui haec
                    paucula tibi exarare, quo meam sempiternam erga te observantiam facilius
                    cognoscere posses. <persName>Augustae</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.4">Isabella of Portugal.</note> abortus<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.5">This son was stillborn. The Empress had seven pregnancies
                        and suffered two miscarriages.</note> nos omnes sollicitos reddidit. Utinam
                    caesari in danda filiis opera melior ei fortuna arrideat, sed deos spero
                    caesari, deo nostro<note type="critic" xml:id="note.6">After this word, a word
                        missing.</note> fore propitios. <persName>Pontifex</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.7">Pope Clement VII.</note> ex Urbanis litteris
                    III. Nonarum Sextilis<note type="critic" xml:id="note.8">3 August.</note>
                    disenteria gravissime laborabat, hominem medici in desperatis habebant, quamvis
                    meliusculus esset factus.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.9">Indeed, he died
                        soon, on 25 September.</note><persName>Aenobarbus</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.10">Hayreddin Barbarossa Pasha.</note> cum classe
                    Turcica <placeName>Zaznithum</placeName> versus navigabat oppugnaturus
                        <placeName>Melitam</placeName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.11"
                        >Malta.</note> incerto tamen rumore. Ex <persName>Siculis</persName>
                    litteris nobis nuntiatum est <persName>Gallum</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.12">King Francis I.</note> misisse ad Turcas Rineonem<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.13">Antonio Rincon (†1541) was an envoy of King
                        Francis I to Szapolyai, later to Sultan Suleiman I and he was sent to
                        Constantinople between 1530 and 1541 several times, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Setton</hi> 1984, passim; and <hi rend="smallcap">Kasza</hi> 2015,
                        91–92 and 156.</note> Hispanum. Item Turcae oratorem redeuntem ex Gallia
                    naufragium fecisse in sirtibus minoribus captum et postea redemptum ad caesarem
                    suum profectum. Audivimus <persName>Gritteum</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.14">Lodovico Gritti.</note><placeName>Albam
                        Graecam</placeName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.15">Belgrade.</note>
                    pervenisse pro componendis inter <persName>regem</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.16">King Ferdinand I.</note> nostrum et
                        <persName>Ioannem</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.17">King John
                        I.</note> rebus. Utinam ex sententia nostra, quod reliquum est, succedat.
                    Ego de Anglicis rebus certior fieri cupio. <persName>Rimoldus</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.18">We do not know him more closely.</note>
                    operam suam tibi praestabit, quo me possis rariora et constantissima docere.
                    Salutabis meo nomine clarissimam <persName>Virginem Lucretiam</persName>.<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.19">Lucretia Caballis (vom Ross).</note> Valere
                    cupio Olaum meum et serenissimae dominae, dominae reginae, dominae nostrae
                    clementissimae pedes deosculor. Vale, Amicorum Optime, et
                        <persName>Bannisio</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.20">Jakob
                        Radich de Bannisis the Younger.</note> me commenda, cui et in primis tibi
                    globum meum curae esse cupio. Si <persName>Rotterodamus</persName> noster in
                    patriam rediit, fac, ex te intelligam. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3"><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> pridie Idus Sextilis 1534.</p>
            </div>
